# uv
.venv/
# uv.lock is intentionally NOT ignored — it's a real, version-controlled
# file per Astral's guidance for applications. See
# https://docs.astral.sh/uv/concepts/projects/sync/#applications-vs-libraries
# for the applications-vs-libraries distinction. Libraries (which are
# installed into other projects' environments) should not commit
# uv.lock; applications (which are deployed as their own environments)
# should. Ossia is an application.

